<h2> Node.Js takeways </h2>

<ol>

<li> Node will aloow the user to run JS on thier computer so they can have acesses to run a server. </li>
<li> It is a very powerful way to run a server and to see the instant results.</li>
<li>  Node.Js is event based. It is also asynchronous when it runs.</li>
<li>  Since it is event based, everything that happens in Node is a event. </li>
<li> Node.Js is really good for building out APIs and other various sites. </li>
<li> Node.Js lets you use any lanuage in the backend. this helps to speed things out on the devopler side.</li>
<li> You can write Node.Js in your command line.</li>

